    {"w":"power","ph":"/ˈpaʊər/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"power","fam":["powers","powered","powerful","powerless","empower","superpower","willpower","horsepower"],"pl":"powers","tn":[],"hi":"शक्ति/ताकत","en":"the ability to do something; strength or authority","ds":"The ability or capacity to do something; strength; authority.","dd":"'Power' refers to physical strength ('muscle power'), authority ('political power'), energy supply ('electrical power'), and mathematical exponents ('2 to the power of 3'). As a verb 'power' means to supply energy to. 'Empower' means to give authority. Many compounds: 'powerhouse', 'willpower', 'horsepower'.","ex":"She uses her power responsibly to help people in need.","exh":"वह जरूरतमंद लोगों की मदद करने के लिए अपनी शक्ति का जिम्मेदारी से उपयोग करती है।","syl":["pow","er"],"syn":["strength","force","energy","authority","control","might","ability","influence","capacity","capability"],"ant":["weakness","powerlessness","inability","subordination","dependence"],"rel":["strength","force","energy","authority","control","ability","influence","electricity","muscle"],"dif":"basic","fr":201,"ew":0.4,"it":"informational","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["the","great","political","economic","military","solar","wind","nuclear","over"],"st":["strength","authority","energy","influence","mathematics"],"cv":["authority use","energy use","mathematical use","'empower' use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"town","ph":"/taʊn/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"town","fam":["towns","township","townspeople","downtown","hometown","town hall","out of town"],"pl":"towns","tn":[],"hi":"कस्बा/नगर","en":"a settlement larger than a village but smaller than a city","ds":"An urban area larger than a village but smaller than a city.","dd":"'Town' refers to an urban settlement larger than a village ('a small town'), the central area of a city ('go to town'), and 'out of town' means away from one's usual location. 'Town hall' is a public meeting building. 'Township' is an administrative division.","ex":"She grew up in a small quiet town near the mountains.","exh":"वह पहाड़ों के पास एक छोटे से शांत कस्बे में पली-बढ़ी।","syl":["town"],"syn":["village","borough","municipality","settlement","township","city","urban area","locality"],"ant":["city","countryside","wilderness","rural area"],"rel":["city","village","street","market","center","local","area","district","suburb"],"dif":"basic","fr":202,"ew":0.2,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"place","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["small","big","old","nearby","border","native","home","center","hall","market"],"st":["settlement","urban area","community","local"],"cv":["settlement use","'go to town' idiom","'out of town' use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"fine","ph":"/faɪn/","pos":"adjective","gr":"modifier","rt":"fine","fam":["finely","finer","finest","refine","define","confine","refined","superfine","fine-tune"],"pl":"","tn":["fine","fines","fined","fining"],"hi":"ठीक/महीन/जुर्माना","en":"of high quality; satisfactory; thin; a penalty payment","ds":"Of high quality; satisfactory; very thin; a penalty payment.","dd":"'Fine' as an adjective means high quality ('fine art'), satisfactory ('I'm fine'), and very thin ('fine thread'). As a noun it is a monetary penalty ('pay a fine'). As a verb it means to impose a financial penalty ('she was fined'). 'Fine-tune' means to make small adjustments.","ex":"She is feeling fine after a good night's sleep and breakfast.","exh":"अच्छी नींद और नाश्ते के बाद वह ठीक महसूस कर रही है।","syl":["fine"],"syn":["good","great","excellent","satisfactory","thin","delicate","penalty","well","okay","splendid"],"ant":["terrible","poor","coarse","thick","bad","ill","sick"],"rel":["good","well","okay","excellent","thin","delicate","quality","penalty","punishment"],"dif":"basic","fr":203,"ew":0.3,"it":"descriptive","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"modifier","dl":["noun","verb"],"co":["I'm","feel","that's","arts","dining","line","print","penalty","absolutely","perfectly"],"st":["quality","satisfaction","fineness","penalty","health"],"cv":["satisfactory use","quality use","thin use","penalty noun use"],"su":["modifier","predicate"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"drive","ph":"/draɪv/","pos":"verb","gr":"predicate","rt":"drive","fam":["drives","drove","driven","driving","driver","driveway","overdriven","hard drive","test drive"],"pl":"","tn":["drive","drives","drove","driven","driving"],"hi":"गाड़ी चलाना/प्रेरित करना","en":"to operate a vehicle; to urge or compel","ds":"To operate and control a vehicle; to force or compel someone.","dd":"'Drive' means to operate a vehicle ('drive a car'), to urge or compel ('drive someone to success'), to hit a ball hard in sports ('drive the ball'), to power ('driven by electricity'), and as a noun to a road leading to a house or an organized effort ('a fundraising drive').","ex":"She drives to work every day because public transport is limited.","exh":"वह हर रोज काम पर गाड़ी चलाकर जाती है क्योंकि सार्वजनिक परिवहन सीमित है।","syl":["drive"],"syn":["operate","steer","propel","compel","motivate","urge","travel","ride","push","pilot"],"ant":["stop","park","halt","discourage","brake","walk","prevent"],"rel":["car","travel","road","motor","steer","ride","motivation","propel","urge","lead"],"dif":"basic","fr":204,"ew":0.2,"it":"action","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"action","spr":"verb","dl":["subject","object","place"],"co":["car","home","work","away","crazy","to","through","safely","carefully","fast","hard"],"st":["vehicle operation","motivation","compulsion","propulsion"],"cv":["vehicle use","motivation use","sports use","noun use (fundraising drive)"],"su":["predicate"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","informal"]},
    {"w":"short","ph":"/ʃɔːrt/","pos":"adjective","gr":"modifier","rt":"short","fam":["shorter","shortest","shortly","shortage","shortfall","shortcut","shorten","shorthand","short-term"],"pl":"","tn":[],"hi":"छोटा/कम","en":"of little length or height; not enough","ds":"Having a small length or height; not lasting long; lacking enough.","dd":"'Short' describes small length ('short hair'), small height ('a short person'), brief duration ('a short break'), and insufficient quantity ('short on time', 'fall short'). Many compounds: 'shortcut', 'short-term', 'shortage'. 'Shortly' means 'soon'. 'Short-circuit' means to cause to fail by bypassing.","ex":"She took a short break between classes to grab a snack.","exh":"उसने नाश्ता लेने के लिए कक्षाओं के बीच एक छोटा ब्रेक लिया।","syl":["short"],"syn":["brief","small","little","low","compact","concise","limited","quick","insufficient","lacking"],"ant":["long","tall","extended","sufficient","abundant","lengthy"],"rel":["brief","quick","small","limited","low","lack","cut","break","time","duration"],"dif":"basic","fr":205,"ew":0.0,"it":"descriptive","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"modifier","dl":["noun"],"co":["very","quite","too","rather","quite","term","cut","break","supply","hair","list"],"st":["length","height","duration","quantity","brevity"],"cv":["length adjective","height adjective","duration adjective","insufficient use"],"su":["modifier"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"sport","ph":"/spɔːrt/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"sport","fam":["sports","sporting","sportsman","sportsmanship","sportswear","sport-specific"],"pl":"sports","tn":[],"hi":"खेल/खेलकूद","en":"physical activity with rules done for enjoyment or competition","ds":"A physical activity with rules done for enjoyment or competition.","dd":"'Sport' refers to organized physical activity ('a sport like football'), fair behavior ('be a good sport'), and informally a person of that type ('he's a good sport'). In American English 'sports' is the more common form. 'Sportsmanship' refers to ethical behavior in sports. Sports can be team or individual.","ex":"She is very passionate about sport and trains every single day.","exh":"वह खेल के बारे में बहुत उत्साही है और हर रोज प्रशिक्षण लेती है।","syl":["sport"],"syn":["game","athletics","recreation","pastime","activity","competition","exercise","leisure","fun"],"ant":["work","study","inactivity","sedentary activity"],"rel":["game","exercise","competition","team","player","fitness","field","court","play","athlete"],"dif":"basic","fr":206,"ew":0.5,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["team","competitive","outdoor","indoor","water","extreme","love","national","star"],"st":["physical activity","competition","recreation","sportsmanship"],"cv":["organized sport use","'good sport' (fair person) use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","informal"]},
    {"w":"money","ph":"/ˈmʌni/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"money","fam":["monetary","moneyed","monies","money-wise","fundraiser","cashier"],"pl":"","tn":[],"hi":"पैसा/धन","en":"coins and banknotes used as a medium of exchange","ds":"Currency used to purchase goods and services; wealth.","dd":"'Money' refers to currency ('save money'), wealth ('she has a lot of money'), and a resource ('money of time' — metaphorical). It is an uncountable noun in most uses. 'Monies' is a formal/legal plural. Many idioms: 'money talks', 'time is money', 'spend money like water', 'money can't buy happiness'.","ex":"She saves a little money each month to prepare for the future.","exh":"वह भविष्य की तैयारी के लिए हर महीने थोड़ा पैसा बचाती है।","syl":["mon","ey"],"syn":["cash","currency","funds","wealth","finance","capital","income","coin","resources","earnings"],"ant":["debt","poverty","deficit","loss","expenses"],"rel":["bank","pay","save","spend","earn","rich","poor","wealth","income","finance"],"dif":"basic","fr":207,"ew":0.4,"it":"informational","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["save","spend","make","earn","need","more","less","enough","lots of","borrow"],"st":["currency","wealth","finance","resource","exchange"],"cv":["currency use","wealth use","'money talks' idiom"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"book","ph":"/bʊk/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"book","fam":["books","booked","booking","booklet","bookshelf","notebook","textbook","bookmark","bookstore"],"pl":"books","tn":["book","books","booked","booking"],"hi":"किताब/बुक करना","en":"a set of written pages bound together; to reserve","ds":"A set of written or printed pages bound together; to reserve a service.","dd":"'Book' as a noun is a bound collection of pages ('read a book'), a record ('the books of a company'), and a file in computing. As a verb it means to reserve ('book a hotel'). 'By the book' means following rules strictly. Many compounds: 'notebook', 'textbook', 'bookshelf'.","ex":"She borrowed an interesting book from the local public library.","exh":"उसने स्थानीय सार्वजनिक पुस्तकालय से एक दिलचस्प किताब उधार ली।","syl":["book"],"syn":["volume","publication","text","manual","novel","guide","script","reserve","schedule","arrange"],"ant":["cancel","give back","verbal","unwritten"],"rel":["read","write","library","author","chapter","page","story","novel","text","publish"],"dif":"basic","fr":208,"ew":0.4,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["read","new","old","favorite","my","the","open","close","club","shelf","store"],"st":["publication","knowledge","reservation","record"],"cv":["publication use","verb use (reserve)","'by the book' idiom"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"name","ph":"/neɪm/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"name","fam":["names","named","naming","namely","nameless","nickname","surname","rename","nameplate","byname"],"pl":"names","tn":["name","names","named","naming"],"hi":"नाम","en":"a word by which a person or thing is known","ds":"A word or term used to identify a person or thing.","dd":"'Name' as a noun refers to an identifying word ('her name is Anna'), a reputation ('make a name for yourself'), and a category ('in the name of justice'). As a verb it means to give a name to ('name the child'), to identify ('name the suspect'), or to appoint ('name her director').","ex":"She gave her daughter a beautiful name with a lovely meaning.","exh":"उसने अपनी बेटी को एक सुंदर अर्थ वाला एक सुंदर नाम दिया।","syl":["name"],"syn":["title","label","designation","term","identity","appellation","nickname","alias","reputation","moniker"],"ant":["anonymity","nameless","unknown","unnaming"],"rel":["label","title","identity","call","reputation","person","brand","word","term","alias"],"dif":"basic","fr":209,"ew":0.2,"it":"informational","rp":"high","cs":"opening","dc":"statement","td":"person","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["first","last","full","my","her","his","their","good","bad","brand","what's your"],"st":["identity","designation","reputation","naming"],"cv":["identifier use","reputation use","verb use (give a name)","'in the name of' idiom"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"send","ph":"/sɛnd/","pos":"verb","gr":"predicate","rt":"send","fam":["sends","sent","sending","sender","resend","transmit"],"pl":"","tn":["send","sends","sent","sending"],"hi":"भेजना","en":"to cause something to go to a destination","ds":"To arrange for something or someone to go to another place.","dd":"'Send' means to cause to go ('send a letter'), to transmit ('send a message'), to dispatch ('send troops'), and to cause to be in a state ('it sent her crazy'). Its irregular past tense is 'sent'. Phrasal verbs: 'send out', 'send back', 'send for', 'send off'.","ex":"She sent a thank-you card to everyone who attended the ceremony.","exh":"उसने समारोह में शामिल होने वाले सभी लोगों को एक धन्यवाद कार्ड भेजा।","syl":["send"],"syn":["dispatch","transmit","deliver","mail","forward","emit","give","pass","issue","release"],"ant":["receive","get","keep","hold","return","take back"],"rel":["give","transfer","deliver","transmit","post","email","pass","forward","carry","ship"],"dif":"basic","fr":210,"ew":0.1,"it":"action","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"action","spr":"verb","dl":["subject","object","indirect object","destination"],"co":["me","you","him","her","them","us","letter","email","message","back","out","off"],"st":["dispatch","transmission","delivery","cause"],"cv":["physical dispatch use","digital message use","'send for' (request) use"],"su":["predicate"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"eye","ph":"/aɪ/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"eye","fam":["eyes","eyed","eyeing","eyebrow","eyelid","eyeball","eyesight","oversight"],"pl":"eyes","tn":[],"hi":"आँख","en":"the organ of sight","ds":"The organ used for seeing; a watchful gaze.","dd":"'Eye' is the organ of vision. Used idiomatically: 'keep an eye on' (watch), 'eye contact', 'see eye to eye' (agree), 'bird's-eye view' (from above). As a verb 'eye' means to watch carefully. 'Eyesight' refers to vision ability.","ex":"She has a sharp eye for noticing important details in her work.","exh":"उसकी काम में महत्वपूर्ण विवरण नोटिस करने की तीखी नजर है।","syl":["eye"],"syn":["sight","gaze","vision","look","observe","watch","attention","perception"],"ant":["blindness","ignore"],"rel":["sight","see","look","watch","vision","focus","attention","observe"],"dif":"basic","fr":211,"ew":0.2,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"person","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["the","good","sharp","keen","naked","right","left","trained","expert","keep an"],"st":["vision","organ","observation","attention","idiom"],"cv":["body part use","'eye for detail' idiom","'keep an eye on' idiom"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","informal"]},
    {"w":"question","ph":"/ˈkwɛstʃən/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"question","fam":["questions","questioned","questioning","questionnaire","questionable"],"pl":"questions","tn":[],"hi":"प्रश्न","en":"a sentence or phrase asking for information","ds":"A sentence used to obtain information or express doubt.","dd":"'Question' is a sentence requesting information. As a verb: to ask for information or express doubt. 'Question mark' is the ? punctuation. Common in learning, inquiry, and debate contexts.","ex":"The student raised a thoughtful question during the science class.","exh":"छात्र ने विज्ञान कक्षा के दौरान एक विचारशील प्रश्न उठाया।","syl":["ques","tion"],"syn":["inquiry","query","issue","matter","doubt","point"],"ant":["answer","reply","solution"],"rel":["answer","ask","inquiry","problem","topic","debate","issue"],"dif":"basic","fr":212,"ew":0.2,"it":"informational","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"question","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["good","important","difficult","key","ask","answer","raise","main","open"],"st":["inquiry","information","doubt","topic"],"cv":["question sentence use","'out of question' use","verb use (interrogate)"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"black","ph":"/blæk/","pos":"adjective","gr":"modifier","rt":"black","fam":["blacks","blacken","blackout","blackboard","blackberry","blackbird","black-and-white","blacklist"],"pl":"","tn":[],"hi":"काला","en":"of the darkest color; without light","ds":"Of the darkest color; having no light or color.","dd":"'Black' describes the darkest possible color resulting from the absence of or complete absorption of light. As a noun it refers to the color black, dark-skinned people (used carefully in context), or the black side in chess. Idioms: 'black market', 'black sheep', 'in the black' (profitable).","ex":"She wore a black dress to the formal evening dinner party.","exh":"उसने औपचारिक शाम के डिनर पार्टी में एक काली पोशाक पहनी।","syl":["black"],"syn":["dark","ebony","jet","sable","obsidian","coal-black","pitch-black","darkest","shadowy"],"ant":["white","light","bright","pale","colorless","clear"],"rel":["dark","night","shadow","color","white","board","market","coffee","cat","bird"],"dif":"basic","fr":213,"ew":0.1,"it":"descriptive","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"modifier","dl":["noun"],"co":["and white","dark","jet","pure","coal","dress","cat","board","market","sheep"],"st":["color","darkness","formal","idiom"],"cv":["color adjective use","'black market' idiom","'black sheep' idiom"],"su":["modifier"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"white","ph":"/waɪt/","pos":"adjective","gr":"modifier","rt":"white","fam":["whites","whiten","whiteness","whiteboard","white-collar","white lie"],"pl":"","tn":[],"hi":"सफेद","en":"of the lightest color; reflecting all light","ds":"Of the lightest possible color; the color of snow.","dd":"'White' describes the lightest color, resulting from reflecting all wavelengths of light ('white snow'). As a noun it refers to the color, the white of an egg, or the light-colored pieces in chess. Idioms: 'white lie' (harmless lie), 'white-collar' (office worker), 'whiteboard'.","ex":"She painted the living room walls white to make them look bigger.","exh":"उसने लिविंग रूम की दीवारों को बड़ा दिखाने के लिए सफेद रंग से रंगा।","syl":["white"],"syn":["pale","light","ivory","cream","snow-white","bleached","chalky","fair","pure","bright"],"ant":["black","dark","colored","stained","impure"],"rel":["light","color","pure","clean","bright","snow","milk","paper","board","collar"],"dif":"basic","fr":214,"ew":0.1,"it":"descriptive","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"modifier","dl":["noun"],"co":["black","and","pure","snow","bright","light","collar","board","lie","shirt"],"st":["color","purity","light","clarity"],"cv":["color adjective use","'white lie' idiom","'white-collar' compound"],"su":["modifier"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"food","ph":"/fuːd/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"food","fam":["foods","foodie","foodstuff","food bank","fast food","food chain","seafood","junk food"],"pl":"foods","tn":[],"hi":"भोजन/खाना","en":"substances consumed to provide nutrition","ds":"Any substance eaten to provide nutrition and energy.","dd":"'Food' refers to any substance consumed by organisms for nutrition ('cook food'). It can be countable ('various foods') or uncountable ('plenty of food'). Idiom: 'food for thought' means something worth considering. Compounds: 'fast food', 'seafood', 'junk food', 'food chain'.","ex":"She always cooks healthy food for her family on weekends.","exh":"वह सप्ताहांत पर अपने परिवार के लिए हमेशा स्वस्थ भोजन बनाती है।","syl":["food"],"syn":["nourishment","nutrition","meal","sustenance","diet","fare","cuisine","provisions","rations","edibles"],"ant":["hunger","starvation","fasting","poison","toxin"],"rel":["eat","meal","cook","nutrition","diet","health","hunger","drink","market","farm"],"dif":"basic","fr":215,"ew":0.5,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["healthy","fresh","good","delicious","fast","junk","home-cooked","enough","organic"],"st":["nutrition","sustenance","cuisine","consumption"],"cv":["nutrition use","'food for thought' idiom","'food chain' compound"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"water","ph":"/ˈwɔːtər/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"water","fam":["waters","watered","watering","waterfall","waterway","underwater","watercolor","watershed","waterproof"],"pl":"waters","tn":["water","waters","watered","watering"],"hi":"पानी/जल","en":"a clear liquid essential for life","ds":"A transparent liquid that forms rain, rivers, and seas; essential for life.","dd":"'Water' is the transparent liquid compound H₂O, essential for life. 'Waters' refers to a body of water ('the Caribbean waters'). As a verb 'water' means to pour water on plants or to add water to dilute. Idioms: 'in hot water' (in trouble), 'water under the bridge' (past problems).","ex":"She drinks at least eight glasses of water every single day.","exh":"वह हर रोज कम से कम आठ गिलास पानी पीती है।","syl":["wa","ter"],"syn":["H2O","liquid","fluid","river","ocean","sea","moisture","hydration","aqua","spring"],"ant":["drought","dryness","fire","land","desert"],"rel":["drink","rain","river","sea","ocean","life","clean","pure","flow","wet"],"dif":"basic","fr":216,"ew":0.3,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["drink","clean","fresh","cold","hot","tap","spring","still","sparkling","deep"],"st":["liquid","life","nature","hydration","essential"],"cv":["liquid use","verb use (water plants)","'in hot water' idiom"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"country","ph":"/ˈkʌntri/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"country","fam":["countries","countrywide","countryside","country-side","fellow country","countrymen","cross-country"],"pl":"countries","tn":[],"hi":"देश/गाँव","en":"a nation with its own government; the rural area","ds":"A nation with its own government and territory; the rural area.","dd":"'Country' refers to a nation ('a foreign country'), rural areas as opposed to cities ('move to the country'), and country music ('listening to country'). 'Countryside' is the rural landscape. 'Countrymen' are fellow citizens. 'Cross-country' refers to going over open terrain.","ex":"She traveled to five different countries during her summer vacation.","exh":"उसने गर्मियों की छुट्टियों के दौरान पाँच अलग-अलग देशों की यात्रा की।","syl":["coun","try"],"syn":["nation","state","land","territory","homeland","rural area","republic","kingdom","countryside"],"ant":["city","urban area","foreign land","abroad"],"rel":["nation","land","state","government","city","travel","flag","border","capital","people"],"dif":"basic","fr":217,"ew":0.3,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"place","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["the","my","native","home","foreign","developing","rich","poor","beautiful","rural"],"st":["nation","geography","rural area","homeland","territory"],"cv":["nation use","rural use","country music use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"stop","ph":"/stɒp/","pos":"verb","gr":"predicate","rt":"stop","fam":["stops","stopped","stopping","stopper","nonstop","unstoppable","bus stop","stopover","stop-motion"],"pl":"","tn":["stop","stops","stopped","stopping"],"hi":"रुकना/बंद करना","en":"to cease moving or operating; to cause to cease","ds":"To cease moving or operating; to bring to an end.","dd":"'Stop' means to cease movement ('stop running'), to end an activity ('stop laughing'), to prevent ('stop them'), and to stay briefly ('stop at a hotel'). It is followed by a gerund ('stop talking') not an infinitive — 'stop to talk' means to pause in order to talk. Many compounds: 'bus stop', 'stop sign'.","ex":"She told the children to stop making noise in the library.","exh":"उसने बच्चों को पुस्तकालय में शोर करना बंद करने के लिए कहा।","syl":["stop"],"syn":["cease","halt","end","finish","pause","quit","terminate","freeze","stand still","prevent"],"ant":["start","begin","continue","go on","proceed","run","keep going"],"rel":["end","finish","pause","halt","cease","prevent","brake","quit","break","rest"],"dif":"basic","fr":218,"ew":0.1,"it":"action","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"action","spr":"verb","dl":["subject","gerund","object"],"co":["now","it","talking","working","doing","trying","by","over","please","immediately"],"st":["cessation","halt","prevention","end","pause"],"cv":["cease use","prevent use","brief stay use","'bus stop' compound"],"su":["predicate"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"face","ph":"/feɪs/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"face","fam":["faces","faced","facing","face-to-face","facebook","faceless","surface","interface","façade"],"pl":"faces","tn":["face","faces","faced","facing"],"hi":"चेहरा/सामना करना","en":"the front part of the head; to confront","ds":"The front part of a person's head; to confront a problem.","dd":"'Face' as a noun means the front of the head ('her smiling face'), the surface of something ('the face of a coin'), or an expression ('make a face'). As a verb it means to confront ('face the problem') or to turn toward ('face the window'). 'Face-to-face' means in person.","ex":"She faced her fears and decided to speak in front of the audience.","exh":"उसने अपने डर का सामना किया और दर्शकों के सामने बोलने का फैसला किया।","syl":["face"],"syn":["front","expression","visage","countenance","confront","meet","deal with","address","tackle"],"ant":["back","avoid","run away","ignore","evade"],"rel":["head","smile","look","expression","front","confront","deal","surface","meet"],"dif":"basic","fr":219,"ew":0.3,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"person","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["the","her","his","straight","pretty","to-face","mask","value","challenge","reality"],"st":["facial feature","expression","surface","confrontation"],"cv":["body part use","confront use","'face value' use","'face-to-face' compound"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"door","ph":"/dɔːr/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"door","fam":["doors","doorway","doorbell","doorstep","doorman","doorknob","outdoors","indoor","doormat"],"pl":"doors","tn":[],"hi":"दरवाज़ा","en":"a movable barrier used for entering or exiting a room","ds":"A movable panel that opens and closes an entrance.","dd":"'Door' is a movable barrier at an entrance ('open the door'). 'Doorway' is the opening. 'Doorstep' is the step at the entrance. 'Next door' means the adjacent place. 'Open doors' figuratively means opportunities. 'Door to door' means from one place to another.","ex":"She knocked on the door and waited patiently for an answer.","exh":"उसने दरवाजे पर दस्तक दी और धैर्यपूर्वक जवाब का इंतजार किया।","syl":["door"],"syn":["entrance","gateway","opening","portal","entryway","hatchway","exit","access"],"ant":["wall","barrier","sealed"],"rel":["room","house","open","close","enter","exit","knock","key","lock","window"],"dif":"basic","fr":220,"ew":0.1,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"place","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["the","open","close","front","back","next","knock","answer","lock","bell"],"st":["entrance","access","barrier","opportunity (figurative)"],"cv":["physical door use","'next door' use","'open doors' (opportunity)"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","informal"]},
    {"w":"walk","ph":"/wɔːk/","pos":"verb","gr":"predicate","rt":"walk","fam":["walks","walked","walking","walker","walkway","sidewalk","catwalk","walkout","crosswalk"],"pl":"","tn":["walk","walks","walked","walking"],"hi":"चलना/टहलना","en":"to move on foot at a normal pace","ds":"To move on foot at a moderate pace; to take a stroll.","dd":"'Walk' means to move on foot ('walk to school'), to accompany on foot ('walk the dog'), and as a noun a journey on foot ('go for a walk'). Phrasal verbs: 'walk away', 'walk out', 'walk through'. 'Walk of life' means one's occupation or social status.","ex":"She walks to the nearby market every morning for fresh produce.","exh":"वह ताजा उत्पाद के लिए हर सुबह पास के बाजार तक पैदल जाती है।","syl":["walk"],"syn":["stroll","march","stride","pace","amble","hike","wander","tread","trek","saunter"],"ant":["run","stay","stop","sit","drive","remain"],"rel":["run","go","move","step","pace","stroll","path","road","feet","exercise"],"dif":"basic","fr":221,"ew":0.2,"it":"action","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"action","spr":"verb","dl":["subject","place","object"],"co":["to","away","out","in","around","through","on","slowly","fast","alone","together"],"st":["movement","exercise","journey","stroll"],"cv":["movement use","'walk the dog' use","'walk of life' idiom"],"su":["predicate"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","informal"]},
    {"w":"white","ph":"/waɪt/","pos":"adjective","gr":"modifier","rt":"white","fam":["whites","whiten","whiteness","whiteboard","white-collar"],"pl":"","tn":[],"hi":"सफेद","en":"of the lightest color; without darkness","ds":"Reflecting all wavelengths of visible light; the color of snow.","dd":"Duplication removed — see entry at fr:214. This entry is 'white' at higher frequency in adjectival use. White often appears in compounds and idioms: 'whiteboard', 'white-collar worker', 'white lie'.","ex":"She wore a white shirt to the formal business presentation.","exh":"उसने औपचारिक व्यावसायिक प्रस्तुति के लिए एक सफेद शर्ट पहनी।","syl":["white"],"syn":["pale","light","ivory","cream","snow-white","fair","bleached"],"ant":["black","dark","stained"],"rel":["light","color","pure","snow","clean","board","collar","lie"],"dif":"basic","fr":222,"ew":0.0,"it":"descriptive","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"modifier","dl":["noun"],"co":["black","pure","bright","board","lie","collar","shirt","paper"],"st":["color","purity","clarity","compound use"],"cv":["color adjective use","compound (whiteboard)","'white lie' use"],"su":["modifier"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"life","ph":"/laɪf/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"life","fam":["lives","lively","lifelike","lifetime","lifestyle","lifelong","midlife","afterlife","wildlife"],"pl":"lives","tn":[],"hi":"जीवन/ज़िंदगी","en":"the condition of being alive; the period between birth and death","ds":"The condition that distinguishes organisms from non-living matter; one's existence.","dd":"'Life' refers to the condition of being alive ('signs of life'), a person's existence ('her life'), the period of time something lasts ('the life of a battery'), and a way of living ('a good life'). Plural 'lives' refers to individual existences. Many compounds: 'lifestyle', 'lifelong', 'wildlife'.","ex":"She believes that every life is precious and deserves respect.","exh":"वह मानती है कि हर जीवन अनमोल है और सम्मान का पात्र है।","syl":["life"],"syn":["existence","living","being","lifetime","vitality","biography","experience","animation"],"ant":["death","non-existence","inanimate","lifeless"],"rel":["live","death","birth","time","human","person","experience","nature","spirit","soul"],"dif":"basic","fr":223,"ew":0.9,"it":"emotional","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["your","her","his","their","my","good","full","long","entire","whole","daily"],"st":["existence","living","experience","vitality","biography"],"cv":["biological life use","personal existence use","'come to life' use","'way of life' use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"idea","ph":"/aɪˈdɪə/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"idea","fam":["ideas","ideal","idealistic","idealize","idealism","ideology","ideation"],"pl":"ideas","tn":[],"hi":"विचार/सुझाव","en":"a thought or suggestion formed in the mind","ds":"A thought, plan, or suggestion formed in the mind.","dd":"'Idea' refers to a mental concept ('have an idea'), a plan ('a good idea'), or an opinion ('no idea'). 'Have no idea' means to be completely unaware. 'That's the idea' confirms understanding. An 'ideal' is a perfect standard. 'Idealism' is devotion to ideals.","ex":"She came up with a brilliant idea for improving the team process.","exh":"उसने टीम की प्रक्रिया को बेहतर बनाने के लिए एक शानदार विचार सोचा।","syl":["i","de","a"],"syn":["thought","concept","notion","plan","suggestion","proposal","impression","opinion","view","inspiration"],"ant":["ignorance","blankness","no thought","confusion"],"rel":["think","concept","thought","plan","propose","suggest","believe","opinion","theory"],"dif":"basic","fr":224,"ew":0.4,"it":"informational","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective","clause"],"co":["good","great","brilliant","new","fresh","bad","no","any","the","main","creative"],"st":["thought","concept","plan","suggestion","creativity"],"cv":["mental concept use","'have an idea' use","'no idea' (unaware) use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"table","ph":"/ˈteɪbəl/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"table","fam":["tables","tablecloth","tablespoon","timetable","turntable","tablet","database"],"pl":"tables","tn":["table","tables","tabled","tabling"],"hi":"मेज/तालिका","en":"a piece of furniture with a flat top; an organized set of data","ds":"A piece of furniture with a flat top used for eating or working; an organized data set.","dd":"'Table' as a noun means a flat-surfaced furniture piece ('sit at the table'), an organized display of data ('a table of results'), and in British English as a verb means to propose for discussion ('table a motion'). 'Timetable' is a schedule. 'Turn the tables' means to reverse the situation.","ex":"She cleared the table after dinner and started washing the dishes.","exh":"उसने रात के खाने के बाद मेज साफ की और बर्तन धोने लगी।","syl":["ta","ble"],"syn":["desk","counter","surface","chart","diagram","list","schedule","timetable","worksheet"],"ant":["floor","ceiling","wall","remove from agenda"],"rel":["chair","food","meal","desk","data","list","schedule","surface","flat","eating"],"dif":"basic","fr":225,"ew":0.1,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["dinner","kitchen","the","data","time","set","clear","sit at","round","long"],"st":["furniture","data display","schedule","surface"],"cv":["furniture use","data table use","'turn the tables' idiom"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"mother","ph":"/ˈmʌðər/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"mother","fam":["mothers","motherly","motherhood","motherland","mother-tongue","godmother","stepmother"],"pl":"mothers","tn":[],"hi":"माँ/माता","en":"a female parent","ds":"A female parent; a woman who has given birth to a child.","dd":"'Mother' refers to a female parent ('call my mother'), as a title ('Mother Teresa'), or as an adjective meaning main or original ('mother tongue', 'mother country'). 'Motherland' is one's native country. 'Motherly' means caring like a mother. Many cultural and symbolic associations exist.","ex":"She calls her mother every evening to talk and catch up.","exh":"वह बात करने और अपडेट लेने के लिए हर शाम अपनी माँ को फोन करती है।","syl":["moth","er"],"syn":["mom","mum","mama","parent","matriarch","dam","origin","source","founder"],"ant":["father","child","daughter","son"],"rel":["parent","family","father","child","baby","love","care","home","language","country"],"dif":"basic","fr":226,"ew":0.9,"it":"emotional","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"person","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["my","her","his","their","good","single","working","tongue","country","land","nature"],"st":["parent","care","love","origin","family"],"cv":["female parent use","'mother tongue' compound","'mother country' use","title use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"father","ph":"/ˈfɑːðər/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"father","fam":["fathers","fatherly","fatherhood","fatherland","godfather","stepfather"],"pl":"fathers","tn":[],"hi":"पिता/पिताजी","en":"a male parent","ds":"A male parent; a man who has children.","dd":"'Father' refers to a male parent ('her father'), a title for priests ('Father James'), and a creator or originator ('the father of medicine'). 'Fatherland' is one's native country. 'Fatherly' means like a caring father. 'The Founding Fathers' are the founders of the US.","ex":"Her father taught her to be strong, kind, and always honest.","exh":"उसके पिता ने उसे मजबूत, दयालु और हमेशा ईमानदार रहना सिखाया।","syl":["fa","ther"],"syn":["dad","papa","parent","patriarch","sire","origin","founder","creator","priest"],"ant":["mother","child","son","daughter"],"rel":["parent","family","mother","child","love","care","home","ancestor","history"],"dif":"basic","fr":227,"ew":0.8,"it":"emotional","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"person","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["my","her","his","their","good","single","working","founder","holy","godfather"],"st":["parent","care","origin","family","authority"],"cv":["male parent use","religious title use","'father of' (creator) use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"friend","ph":"/frɛnd/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"friend","fam":["friends","friendly","friendship","unfriendly","befriend","friendless","best friend","girlfriend","boyfriend"],"pl":"friends","tn":[],"hi":"दोस्त/मित्र","en":"a person with whom one has a bond of mutual affection","ds":"A person with whom one has a bond of affection and trust.","dd":"'Friend' refers to a person one knows and likes ('her close friend'), a supporter ('a friend of the arts'), and on social media, a connection ('friend request'). 'Friendly' means kind and pleasant. 'Befriend' means to act as a friend to. 'Best friend' is the closest friend.","ex":"She introduced her old school friend to all her new colleagues.","exh":"उसने अपने पुराने स्कूल के दोस्त को अपने सभी नए सहयोगियों से मिलवाया।","syl":["friend"],"syn":["companion","ally","associate","colleague","comrade","buddy","pal","confidant","acquaintance"],"ant":["enemy","foe","rival","stranger","opponent","adversary"],"rel":["companion","trust","love","support","share","bond","relationship","loyalty","kindness"],"dif":"basic","fr":228,"ew":0.8,"it":"emotional","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"person","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective","preposition"],"co":["good","close","best","old","new","mutual","make","childhood","dear","long-time"],"st":["affection","companionship","trust","social bond","support"],"cv":["companion use","'a friend of' (supporter) use","social media friend use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","informal"]},
    {"w":"love","ph":"/lʌv/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"love","fam":["loves","loved","loving","lover","lovely","loveless","beloved","self-love","lovelorn"],"pl":"","tn":["love","loves","loved","loving"],"hi":"प्यार/प्रेम","en":"a deep affection and caring for someone","ds":"An intense feeling of deep affection; to feel deep affection for.","dd":"'Love' as a noun means a deep affection ('love for family'), a romantic passion ('fall in love'), and in sports a score of zero ('love-fifteen' in tennis). As a verb it means to have deep affection for ('I love you') or to greatly enjoy ('she loves reading'). 'Lovely' means pleasant or attractive.","ex":"She shows love and kindness to everyone she meets every day.","exh":"वह हर रोज हर उस व्यक्ति को प्यार और दया दिखाती है जिससे वह मिलती है।","syl":["love"],"syn":["affection","adore","care","devotion","fondness","passion","warmth","cherish","worship","tenderness"],"ant":["hate","dislike","loathe","despise","indifference","hatred"],"rel":["care","affection","family","friend","heart","feeling","bond","relationship","kindness","warmth"],"dif":"basic","fr":229,"ew":1.0,"it":"emotional","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["true","unconditional","fall in","deep","my","her","his","their","show","give","feel"],"st":["emotion","affection","passion","devotion","romance"],"cv":["affection noun use","romantic use","verb use","'in love' expression","sports zero use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"mind","ph":"/maɪnd/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"mind","fam":["minds","minded","minding","mindful","mindless","mindfulness","open-minded","remind","reminded"],"pl":"minds","tn":["mind","minds","minded","minding"],"hi":"मन/दिमाग/आपत्ति करना","en":"the element enabling thought and consciousness; to object to","ds":"The faculty of consciousness and thought; to feel concern or objection.","dd":"'Mind' as a noun refers to the seat of thought and consciousness ('open your mind'), a person's memory ('keep in mind'), and an opinion ('speak your mind'). As a verb it means to object to ('do you mind?'), to pay attention ('mind the gap'), or to take care of ('mind the children'). 'Mind-blowing' means astonishing.","ex":"She always keeps an open mind when learning about new ideas.","exh":"वह नए विचारों के बारे में सीखते समय हमेशा खुले दिमाग रखती है।","syl":["mind"],"syn":["brain","intellect","thought","consciousness","opinion","psyche","soul","intelligence","attitude","care"],"ant":["body","ignore","neglect","carelessness","mindlessness"],"rel":["brain","thought","think","conscience","opinion","idea","focus","attention","remember"],"dif":"basic","fr":230,"ew":0.4,"it":"informational","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"person","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective","object"],"co":["open","in","keep","change","make up","speak your","peace of","state of","never","out of"],"st":["consciousness","thought","opinion","objection","carefulness"],"cv":["consciousness use","object use ('do you mind?')","'keep in mind' use","'mind the gap' use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"dream","ph":"/driːm/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"dream","fam":["dreams","dreamed","dreamt","dreaming","dreamer","dreamland","dreamlike","daydream"],"pl":"dreams","tn":["dream","dreams","dreamed/dreamt","dreaming"],"hi":"सपना/सपने देखना","en":"a series of images during sleep; an aspiration","ds":"Images and thoughts experienced during sleep; an aspiration.","dd":"'Dream' as a noun means mental images during sleep ('a strange dream'), a long-held hope ('her dream is to travel the world'). As a verb it means to experience dreams while sleeping or to imagine ('dream big'). Both 'dreamed' and 'dreamt' are acceptable past forms. 'Daydream' means pleasant fantasizing while awake.","ex":"She has always had a dream of starting her own successful business.","exh":"उसका हमेशा से अपना सफल व्यवसाय शुरू करने का सपना रहा है।","syl":["dream"],"syn":["vision","aspiration","goal","hope","fantasy","wish","ambition","imagination","reverie","ideal"],"ant":["nightmare","reality","certainty","wakefulness"],"rel":["sleep","hope","wish","imagine","aspire","goal","vision","fantasy","ambition","future"],"dif":"basic","fr":231,"ew":0.8,"it":"emotional","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["my","her","his","their","big","sweet","wild","come true","pursue","chase","beyond"],"st":["aspiration","sleep vision","hope","imagination","goal"],"cv":["sleep vision use","aspiration use","verb use","'dream come true' idiom"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"peace","ph":"/piːs/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"peace","fam":["peaceful","peacefully","peacemaker","peacetime","peace-loving","inner peace"],"pl":"","tn":[],"hi":"शांति/चैन","en":"freedom from disturbance; a state of tranquility","ds":"A state of freedom from conflict, trouble, or disturbance.","dd":"'Peace' refers to freedom from war ('a peace treaty'), tranquility ('peace of mind'), and harmony ('live in peace'). It is an uncountable noun in most uses. 'Peace of mind' means mental calm. 'Rest in peace (RIP)' is used for the deceased. 'Make peace' means to end a conflict.","ex":"She felt a deep sense of peace and joy after meditation.","exh":"ध्यान के बाद उसे गहरी शांति और खुशी की अनुभूति हुई।","syl":["peace"],"syn":["tranquility","serenity","harmony","calm","quiet","stillness","concord","truce","accord","rest"],"ant":["war","conflict","noise","chaos","disturbance","strife","turmoil","discord"],"rel":["calm","quiet","harmony","rest","serenity","gentle","still","stable","safe","happy"],"dif":"basic","fr":232,"ew":0.8,"it":"emotional","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["world","inner","peaceful","of mind","process","treaty","agreement","keeping","make","at"],"st":["tranquility","harmony","freedom from conflict","spirituality"],"cv":["freedom from war use","tranquility use","'peace of mind' use","'make peace' use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"hour","ph":"/ˈaʊər/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"hour","fam":["hours","hourly","half-hour","quarter hour","rush hour","after hours","24-hour"],"pl":"hours","tn":[],"hi":"घंटा","en":"a period of sixty minutes","ds":"A unit of time equal to sixty minutes.","dd":"'Hour' is a unit of time consisting of 60 minutes. 'Hours' can mean a long time ('waited for hours') or working hours ('office hours'). '24-hour' means continuous. 'Rush hour' is the busy traffic period. 'After hours' means after official closing time. The adjective 'hourly' means every hour.","ex":"She spends at least one hour every day reading something educational.","exh":"वह हर रोज कम से कम एक घंटा कुछ शैक्षणिक पढ़ने में बिताती है।","syl":["hour"],"syn":["60 minutes","period","time","span","stretch","session","interval","unit of time"],"ant":["instant","second","minute","moment"],"rel":["time","minute","day","week","clock","schedule","period","duration"],"dif":"basic","fr":233,"ew":0.0,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"time","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["one","two","three","an","every","per","office","rush","spare","after","working"],"st":["time unit","duration","period","schedule"],"cv":["time unit use","'rush hour' compound","'after hours' use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"feel","ph":"/fiːl/","pos":"verb","gr":"predicate","rt":"feel","fam":["feels","felt","feeling","feelings","heartfelt"],"pl":"","tn":["feel","feels","felt","feeling"],"hi":"महसूस करना","en":"to be aware of a sensation or emotion","ds":"To experience a physical sensation or emotional state.","dd":"'Feel' is a linking verb expressing emotion or sensation. Used with adjectives ('feel happy'), to express opinions ('feel that'), and for physical touch. Its past tense 'felt' is irregular. 'Feel like' means to want or to seem similar to.","ex":"She feels very confident about her chances in the upcoming competition.","exh":"उसे आगामी प्रतियोगिता में अपनी संभावनाओं के बारे में बहुत आत्मविश्वास है।","syl":["feel"],"syn":["sense","experience","perceive","believe","notice","think","touch"],"ant":["ignore","be numb","be indifferent"],"rel":["sense","emotion","touch","perceive","think","seem","notice"],"dif":"basic","fr":234,"ew":0.7,"it":"emotional","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"verb","dl":["subject","adjective","clause"],"co":["good","better","free","happy","sad","like","ready","comfortable","confident"],"st":["emotion","perception","sensation","opinion","touch"],"cv":["emotion use","touch use","'feel like' (want) use","linking verb use"],"su":["predicate"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"week","ph":"/wiːk/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"week","fam":["weeks","weekly","weekday","weekend","midweek","two-week","fortnight"],"pl":"weeks","tn":[],"hi":"हफ्ता/सप्ताह","en":"a period of seven consecutive days","ds":"A period of seven days; usually from Monday to Sunday.","dd":"'Week' is a seven-day period ('this week', 'next week'). 'Weekday' refers to Monday through Friday. 'Weekend' is Saturday and Sunday. 'Weekly' means happening every week. 'Fortnight' (British) means two weeks. 'Week in, week out' means repeatedly every week.","ex":"She exercises three times a week to stay healthy and active.","exh":"वह स्वस्थ और सक्रिय रहने के लिए सप्ताह में तीन बार व्यायाम करती है।","syl":["week"],"syn":["seven days","seven-day period","weekday","the week","sennight"],"ant":["day","month","year","moment","instant"],"rel":["day","month","year","weekend","daily","schedule","time","calendar","working","next"],"dif":"basic","fr":235,"ew":0.0,"it":"informational","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"time","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["last","next","this","every","once a","twice a","per","the coming","current","working"],"st":["time unit","schedule","period","duration"],"cv":["seven-day unit use","'weekend' compound","'weekly' adjective use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"true","ph":"/truː/","pos":"adjective","gr":"modifier","rt":"true","fam":["truth","truly","truer","truest","untrue","truthful","come true","true-blue"],"pl":"","tn":[],"hi":"सच/सही","en":"in accordance with fact or reality; genuine","ds":"Corresponding to reality; honest; genuine.","dd":"'True' means accurate or factual ('a true story'), loyal ('a true friend'), genuine ('true feelings'), and in geometry exactly level. 'Come true' means to happen as hoped. 'True-blue' means genuinely loyal. 'Truly' is the adverb. 'Truth' is the noun.","ex":"She always tells the true story even if it makes people uncomfortable.","exh":"वह हमेशा सच्ची कहानी बताती है चाहे इससे लोग असहज क्यों न हों।","syl":["true"],"syn":["accurate","correct","genuine","real","factual","honest","sincere","authentic","valid","loyal"],"ant":["false","untrue","fake","dishonest","incorrect","inaccurate","disloyal"],"rel":["fact","real","honest","genuine","correct","truth","accurate","faithful","loyal","valid"],"dif":"basic","fr":236,"ew":0.4,"it":"logical","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"modifier","dl":["noun","be"],"co":["that's","not","very","so","it's","become","come","totally","absolutely","always"],"st":["truth","accuracy","genuineness","loyalty","reality"],"cv":["factual use","genuine use","'come true' use","loyal use"],"su":["modifier","predicate"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"job","ph":"/dʒɒb/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"job","fam":["jobs","jobless","job market","job seeker","full-time job","part-time job"],"pl":"jobs","tn":[],"hi":"नौकरी/काम","en":"a paid position of employment; a task","ds":"A regular paid occupation; a specific piece of work.","dd":"'Job' refers to paid employment ('she got a new job'), a specific task ('do a good job'), and responsibility ('it's your job'). Idiom: 'job well done' means good work. 'Jobless' means unemployed. 'Job market' refers to the availability of employment.","ex":"She got a great job at a technology company after graduation.","exh":"स्नातक होने के बाद उसे एक तकनीकी कंपनी में एक बेहतरीन नौकरी मिली।","syl":["job"],"syn":["work","employment","occupation","position","role","career","task","assignment","profession","duty"],"ant":["unemployment","leisure","vacation","hobby","retirement"],"rel":["work","career","profession","role","pay","hire","skill","company","task","office"],"dif":"basic","fr":237,"ew":0.3,"it":"informational","rp":"high","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"general","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["good","new","full-time","part-time","my","her","get a","find a","dream","demanding"],"st":["employment","occupation","task","responsibility"],"cv":["employment use","task use","'job well done' idiom"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
    {"w":"son","ph":"/sʌn/","pos":"noun","gr":"subject","rt":"son","fam":["sons","stepson","grandson","only son","son-in-law"],"pl":"sons","tn":[],"hi":"बेटा","en":"a male child in relation to his parents","ds":"A male child in relation to his parents; a boy.","dd":"'Son' refers to a male child ('her son is ten'), a male member of a group ('son of the church'), and in religious usage ('the Son of God'). 'Son-in-law' is the husband of one's child. 'Grandson' is a son's son. 'My son' is a form of address to a young man.","ex":"She is so proud of her son who works as a doctor.","exh":"वह अपने बेटे पर बहुत गर्व करती है जो एक डॉक्टर के रूप में काम करता है।","syl":["son"],"syn":["boy","male child","junior","offspring","kid","lad","youth","scion","heir"],"ant":["daughter","mother","father","parent"],"rel":["child","family","parent","mother","father","boy","grandson","daughter","love"],"dif":"basic","fr":238,"ew":0.7,"it":"emotional","rp":"medium","cs":"any","dc":"statement","td":"person","spr":"subject","dl":["verb","adjective"],"co":["my","her","his","their","young","oldest","youngest","only","adult","grown-up"],"st":["male child","family relation","offspring","heir"],"cv":["male child use","'son of' (member of)","religious use"],"su":["subject","object"],"wuc":["daily conversation","writing","formal","informal"]},
